items.name: Mining Light
items.item_description: For Engineers with bright ideas.

items.name: Prussian Pickelhaube
items.item_description:
A relic from one war brought into another.
Your enemy will get the point.

items.name: Batter's Helmet
items.item_description: You'll be batting a thousand (skulls in) when you don this red piece of plastic!

items.name: Trophy Belt
items.item_description:
Any old sap can pull teeth from a dead crocodile.
It takes a man to pull teeth from a live one.

items.name: Soldier's Stash
items.item_description: This hat does not in any way, shape, or form, promote smoking or gambling.

items.name: Fancy Fedora
items.item_description: This smooth, suave, silk-lined beauty can turn any amateur backstabber into a handsome rogue.

items.item_description: Though it looks like a simple ten-gallon hat, this modern feat of engineering actually contains more moving parts than a level 2 Sentry Gun.

items.name: Officer's Ushanka
items.item_description:
This hat was made of bear hands.
That bear was killed with bare hands.

items.name: Tough Guy's Toque
items.item_description: Because when you're the toughest Mother Hubbard in the fort, nobody's criticizing your fashion sense.

items.name: Stainless Pot
items.item_description:
Protects cranium from bullets and shrapnel.
Also heats soup.

items.name: Respectless Rubber Glove
items.item_description: It doesn't matter how much people respect you when they're on fire.

items.item_description: You wouldn't mind if I read this top secret document with my beard, would you?

items.name: Otolaryngologist's Mirror
items.item_description: We can't pronounce it either.

items.name: Bonk Helm
items.item_description: When drinking one radioactive beverage at a time is not enough.

items.name: Ye Olde Baker Boy
items.item_description: Extra! Extra! You're frickin' dead!

items.item_description:
For when you wish your head was a little taller,
but just as round on top.

items.name: Professional's Panama
items.item_description: A polite, efficient hat to wear when killing everyone you meet.

items.item_description: Only a master of Jarate earns the right to wear this once-white bandanna, stained yellow from the rigors of a harsh training regimen.

items.name: Baseball Bill's Sports Shine
items.item_description: Everyone knows that speed is a Scout's best friend. Why weigh yourself down with bulky hats when you can break the sound barrier without them?

items.name: Mildly Disturbing Halloween Mask
items.item_description: Brown paper never looked so mildly disturbing.

items.item_description: Way way more ghastly.

items.item_description:
His bullet was close.
I lost my hat.
My bullet was closer.
He lost his head.

items.item_description: Sometimes you just need a little less hat.

items.name: Web Easteregg Medal
items.item_description: Given to those few brave soldiers whom stood guard valiantly without sleep, nourishment, or a social life.

items.name: CheatDetectedMinor
items.item_name:
Your account has been flagged for circumventing the item distribution system. We have removed the items that were illegally obtained.

Future violations will result in the loss of all your items.

items.name: CheatDetectedMajor
items.item_name:
Your account has been flagged for circumventing the item distribution system. We have removed all items in your inventory.

Future violations may result in your account being disabled.

items.name: CheatDetectedHonesty
items.item_name:
Congratulations! Your Honesty has been rewarded with a new hat!

(Some other players were less scrupulous, and have been less fortunate)

items.name: Honest Halo
items.item_description: Though some would stop at nothing to achieve hats, you remained resolute and incorruptible in your quest for head decorations. For that, you have been rewarded.

items.name: L4D Hat
items.item_description: Left 4 You.

Provides an offensive buff that causes
nearby team members to do mini-crits.

items.name: The Chargin' Targe
items.item_description:
Alt-Fire: Gain increased attack power by
charging toward your enemies.

items.name: The Eyelander
items.item_description:
This weapon has a large melee range.
Gives increased speed and health
with every head you take.

items.name: Soldier Samurai Hat
items.item_description:
A Haiku for war.
To defeat one's enemies.
Honor the crocket.

items.item_description: Perfect for exploring the outback and the inside of people's heads.

The ultimate in semi-concealed weaponry.
There's no question you need this gun,
the only question is: where will you keep it?

Combines style with stopping power.
Long exclusive to Freelance Police,
now available for other blood-thirsty mercenaries.

Expertly crafted headwear from cruelty-free farms
in the Philippines. Hollowed-out skull casing wicks
moisture away when in the heat of battle.

items.name: Employee Badge C
items.item_description: Even though you were late to the party, you were still the life of it.

items.item_description:
Don't leave your friends hanging.

This is a press-and-hold taunt. Hold down the action slot key to remain in the taunt's pose.

items.name: Employee Badge Plat
items.item_description: A true warrior's medal, given to those who fought before the battle even started.

items.name: Pyro Monocle
items.item_description: The most distinguished tape-on fire-retardant facial hair available, for the discerning gentleman of conflagration.

items.name: Medic Goggles
items.item_description: Nothing

items.name: Engineer Earmuffs
items.item_description: It gets difficult trying to calculate the total external applied torque to a body's rotational motion through its moment of momentum vector while the distracting sounds of gunfire and death are all around you. Build a better, safer machine with the silence of the Safe'n'sound!

items.name: Demoman Tricorne

Three sharp corners mean one sharp hat.
Don't poke your eye out.

items.name: Spy Beret
items.item_description: Because real espionage is an artform.

items.item_description: It costs $400,000 to wear this bandanna for 12 seconds.
